commentary: Dilshan to Williamson, OUT Williamson falls to a really poor ball! It was so short and down leg side as well, might have just bounced a bit more, is all. Williamson went back to pull but seemed to be cramped for room and ended up gloving it. Chandimal juggled it a little down leg side before taking the catch. I think that went off the bottom part of the glove, bounced off Williamson's thigh, then bounced off the keeper's thigh before finally landing in his gloves.

commentary: Henry to Mathews, OUT taken. Henry Nicholls has taken another pressure catch. Mathews perishes, how big is that? Short ball on off, Mathews executes a lovely pull but just did not get as much as he would have wanted. It travels high in the air and Nicholls settles himself at the square leg boundary, takes a catch over his head. Would have gone for six had he not got a hand on it. The bat face just turned in his hands
